#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:1
msgid "Scheduling Training Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:3
msgid ""
"The Program Manager collects availability from Instructor Trainers and "
"generates a four month training calendar (January-April, May-August, "
"September-December) three times a year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:5
msgid ""
"Trainees will be asked for their availability in October, March, and July"
" for each four month block, and a calendar will be published 6-8 weeks "
"before each four month block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:7
msgid ""
"Once the calendar is confirmed, the Program Manager updates it on the "
"Member information page and on the internal Carpentries staff Zoom "
"calendars. The Workshop Administration Team will create events in AMY for"
" each of these scheduled trainings.  The Workshop Administration Team "
"will also create an Eventbrite registration page for each event and set "
"up surveys in Survey Monkey for each event.  Lastly, the Workshop "
"Administration Team will reserve Zoom Room 1 for each event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:9
msgid "For Online Training Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:11
msgid ""
"Trainees for each event may be a mix of member-affiliated and non-member "
"affiliated (open training) applicants. Seats are first opened to member-"
"affiliated applicants. One month before the event, remaining seats are "
"offered to open training applicants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:13
msgid ""
"The Director of Memberships or the Administrative Specialist notify the "
"Program Manager when new member sites are ready for instructor training "
"in Asana. This includes information about the agreement start and end "
"dates, number of workshops and instructor training seats allowed, and any"
" other special information.  The Administrative Specialist enters this "
"information in AMY.  The Workshop Administration Team creates an "
"Eventbrite registration code for this new membership.  Note the "
"registration codes document is available to Carpentries staff only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:15
msgid ""
"The Program Manager emails member sites to introduce The Carpentries' "
"Instructor Training Program and give their team members the opportunity "
"to join posted training events according to these guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:17
msgid ""
"The Member contact invites their team members to sign up for an event as "
"a team or as individuals. Individuals associated with member sites can "
"sign up for an event at any time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:19
msgid ""
"During the first week of each month, the Workshop Administration Team "
"invites accepted applicants from the open application pool to register "
"for upcoming events. The accepted applicant list is the union of these "
"two queries in AMY:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:21
msgid "State = \"Accepted\" and Matched = \"Unmatched\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:22
msgid "State = \"Accepted\" and Matched = \"Matched trainee, Unmatched training\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:24
msgid ""
"One month before each event the Workshop Administration Team emails the "
"event's Trainers with information about setting up the website and "
"etherpad for the event, and generally preparing to teach."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:26
msgid ""
"Two weeks before each event, the Workshop Administration Team will begin "
"monitoring the event's waitlist.  If there are any cancellations, the "
"seat will be offered to the next person on the waitlist.  If this person "
"does not claim their seat, it will go to the next person, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:28
msgid "One week before each event, the Workshop Administration Team:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:30
msgid ""
"emails all registrants from Eventbrite with information to prepare for "
"the training event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:31
msgid ""
"emails the Trainers with information including Zoom room access and "
"survey results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:33
msgid "During the training event, the Workshop Administration Team:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:34
msgid ""
"enters all registrants into AMY, associating them with the given event "
"and membership."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:35
msgid ""
"contacts trainees missing their application form, asking them to submit "
"it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:37
msgid "After the event, the Workshop Administration Team:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:39
msgid "emails trainees missing applications"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:40
msgid "asks Trainers to send attendance list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/instructor_training/scheduling_training_events.md:41
msgid ""
"records people who completed training and subsequent checkout steps in "
"AMY.  Emails about the training and checkout progress are typically sent "
"to checkout@carpentries.org, a mailbox in Helpscout."
msgstr ""

